------------------------------------------------------------------
Precedence of Variables
------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Environement variables (With EXPORT)
2. terraform.tfvars
3. terraform.tfvars.json
4. *.auto.tfvars
5. -var or -var-file command-line options

------------------------------------------------------------------
HCL
------------------------------------------------------------------
HCL supports 
Expression: (5+1) or (5>1)
Predefined function: split()

------------------------------------------------------------------
Terraform Function types
------------------------------------------------------------------
Numeric
String
Collection
Encoding
FileSystem
Date and time
Hash and Crypto
Ip Network
Type Conversion
------------------------------------------------------------------
Modules
------------------------------------------------------------------
Root Modules ----- Provider
-Child Module
-Child Module
-Child Module

The software delivery life cycle begins
with developers committing code to a central repository
where continuous integration practices trigger tests
in a series of shared environments.
The development environment is where new code
is first integrated.
The next environment may be called staging or QA,
where more advanced testing is performed,
such as user acceptance and systems integration testing.
Finally, fully tested, feature complete code is pushed
to a production environment where it's used by end users.

------------------------------------------------------------------
Automation CI/CD
------------------------------------------------------------------


Dev -> Source control Git -> CI/CD (Jenkins or GitLab) -> DEV, QA, PROD




